century. Rather than a nostalgic criticism of contemporary knighthood, it should be seen as a showcase of the latest ideas on chivalry, written to renew the enthusiasm of the great French princes for a man who was in grave danger of falling out of favour: its purpose was to celebrate and to defend a beleaguered Boucicaut against his critics at the royal court, and to explain his actions as governor of Genoa, his failed crusading enterprises in the Eastern Mediterranean and his unsuccessful efforts to broker a solution to the PapalSchism. CRAIG TAYLOR is a Reader in Medieval History at the University of York; he was Director of its Centre for Medieval Studies from 2010 to 2011 and from 2014 to 2017.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFrench Studies. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aDefending Marshal Boucicaut.  aFrench court.  aFrench nobility.  aFrench princes.  aLivre des fais du bon messire Jehan le Maingre.  aMiddle Ages.  aPapal Schism.  aRenaissance.  aVirtuous Knight.  abiography.  achivalric biography.  achivalric ideals.  achivalry.  acrusading enterprises.  acultural context.  afifteenth century.  ahistorical interpretation.  ahistorical.  aideal knight.  aknight.  amedieval culture.  amedieval history.  anew ideas.  atraditional chivalric values.  atraditional notions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311143102440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787445611?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787445611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787445611/original  a978-3-11-143102-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles